OL,4,CHouse builders 'should drop appalling
OL,5,Cgagging orders'
OL,6, House builders that carry out repairs
OL,7, on newly built homes need to be more
OL,8, open about what work has been required,
OL,9, according to the chairman of
OL,10, Parliament's Housing Committee.
OL,12,FSome home owners say they were asked to
OL,13,Fsign non-disclosure agreements (NDAs)
OL,14,Fas a condition of repairs being done.
OL,16,FThe practice was "appalling" Clive
OL,17,FBetts MP told Radio 4's Money Box
OL,18,Fprogramme.
OL,20,FThe Home Builders Federation said NDAs
OL,21,Fwere "not widely used" by developers.
